<subSubSection id="E8EC777A4F50F80BA1936B7A8B855BAE" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="4C189D7223AE263C7B0702EFD97EB6E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Etymology.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="3738BB2D2C29192D1530BC2928221405" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<normalizedToken id="4D983F27CC40193A0B534AF0D20C45B6" originalValue="“sasi”">&quot;sasi&quot;</normalizedToken>
means bamboo [host plants] and 
<normalizedToken id="BE110ABBB9D63FD7B1999396D89376A5" originalValue="“brevispora”">&quot;brevispora&quot;</normalizedToken>
means shorter ascospores compared to 
<taxonomicName id="D4B8DF0D15793DD711AE13B83D7668CA" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Lachnaceae" genus="L." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="L. novoguineense subsp. var. var. yunnanicum" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="variety" species="novoguineense" subSpecies="var." variety="yunnanicum">L. novoguineense var. yunnanicum</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="0BC26DD4C43BAF8D7233A0346B045C24" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="japanese name">
<paragraph id="BC95DFCBD3E64044EC4E89D02733D30A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Japanese name.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2C36E59C60574342FCC9B8FB826E1A23" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="7B9B65931254900AB6A3A9F5CAF226F9" class="Liliopsida" family="Poaceae" genus="Sasa" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Sasa" order="Poales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Sasa</taxonomicName>
-no-youmou-chawantake.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F5E9656A65A5D5A1A801289C66A3780C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="9D414E1A8FD3AE1FD7BFA4675957BC49" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="758F4288F7DEB843C10716D8F663EADA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Apothecia gregarious, superficial, 0.6-1.3 mm in diameter, short-stipitate, up to 0.8 mm high, pure white, externally covered with long white hairs. Disc concave, yellow to pale orange when fresh and dry. Ectal excipulum 
<emphasis id="6379EC69886E9F24869A8429281F48B3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">textura prismatica</emphasis>
to 
<emphasis id="F1C7AD1035BF39C8F7AB3C349070431E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">t. angularis</emphasis>
, 3-16 
<normalizedToken id="9A9E20FF52DBC9E83E3E539C68264E04" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-10 
<normalizedToken id="BEE46D8509208C51585DC09E3ED9A929" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, hyaline, thin-walled; surface smooth. Medullary excipulum 
<emphasis id="320FAA2D57AE4163F5B06A192D2DDE54" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">textura intricata</emphasis>
of hyaline hyphae up to 2 
<normalizedToken id="F0AB8D2C7CA64AC325321719FED358ED" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide. Hairs straight, delicate, cylindrical with relatively acute apices, up to 190 
<normalizedToken id="C8F4EDA07300979B88732775964D698E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2-3 
<normalizedToken id="4707838F5FB07F27F8530023FC28F42D" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, hyaline, totally granulate, thin-walled; apical cell a little longer than other cells, lacking any crystals, resinous materials, or apical amorphous materials. Asci (79-)82.5-90(-95) 
<normalizedToken id="2AE90D1A054A180727C138F342F9531D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(6-)6.6-8.1(-9) 
<normalizedToken id="B0FE3D492D5FEB74C9BAFF0E9EC1BF8D" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(av. 86 
<normalizedToken id="0CB23C93736EE98E78C1C43E9BA0F435" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
4.0 
<normalizedToken id="0C6FA1C3A56447095DC95F6E6E296E04" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
7.4 
<normalizedToken id="A54365BF4A6232D58A267F8AF8414916" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.8 
<normalizedToken id="C0ED5BFB76D9CB9618578D2CD7A4855E" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 15), 8-spored, cylindrical-clavate; lateral parts sometimes swelling irregularly; pore blue in MLZ without 3% KOH pretreatment; croziers with perforation present at the basal septa. Ascospores (26-)27.9-36.1(-39) 
<normalizedToken id="8D4C68A933301E0C0FBE7AC39571B3BC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
(1.5-)1.7-2 
<normalizedToken id="B85304EF60813EC3B7908E11D864A989" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
(av. 32 
<normalizedToken id="77FDA09E3528C2A07D9BE13B4D9EDDC6" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
4.1 
<normalizedToken id="F9F0184F212BF32FD5A334C8D61B8067" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
1.8 
<normalizedToken id="DAC6C5D328B71CBF7E7FAF3F693A317F" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
0.2 
<normalizedToken id="9125A859893B3DB76A2F524E06F77B3A" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
, n = 17), Q = (13-)15-19.7(-21) (av. 17.5 
<normalizedToken id="4D21C0BFCBDF2FAE1E9040A306C0D6EE" originalValue="±">+/-</normalizedToken>
2.3, n = 17), long fusiform, usually 3-septate, rarely 0- to 2-septate (only observed in TNS-F-81401 because TNS-F-80399 was immature). Paraphyses straight, lanceolate, 2.5-4 
<normalizedToken id="A89205EA3E561C22C4776ADC09FC12A7" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
wide, densely septate, exceeding the asci up to 15 
<normalizedToken id="A95944232957AFFA4347DD45DBAA6204" originalValue="µm">µm</normalizedToken>
. Note that the description is solely based on the holotype because another examined specimen TNS-F-80399 was in bad condition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="3A90B6A9C52E45DE96FE36BE5A6CB7F2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="description">
<paragraph id="488613E198B23F0E0E85B50CD059472F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Culture characteristics.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="824F86CF334DCA1F593602138C7D8A1E" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Colony of NBRC 114475/ TNS-F-81401 on PDA wrinkled. Context cottony and partially funiculose, white, turning ocher at the center; almost ocher except for the white margin from the reverse. Sectors and zonation absent. Aerial mycelium developed throughout the colony, concolous, forming mycelium strands. Margin indistinct, flat and immersed into agar. Soluble pigment absent. Asexual morph absent.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="912A63EF4A86BC2971EE5E8DF0963C73" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="CE7203D98B2A33F054F68A52C3590978" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8C9089F2A191BE376C6055B929D1E845" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Japan (cool-temperate zone, subarctic zone).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="181505AD4622713F16E5300D222CF659" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="69A5BE28431B1D40DB02757D8326B223" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25B3E73446D4D10E807D622B05686C2A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<taxonomicName id="66D08B70CFCE60D24528B2B9477BC1FE" authorityName="Tochihara &amp; Hosoya" authorityYear="2022" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Lachnaceae" genus="Erioscyphella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Erioscyphella sasibrevispora" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="sasibrevispora">
<emphasis id="73371613BC04FB24BA86DB57668722D3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erioscyphella sasibrevispora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName id="326C45D71B6DCC9062074FA678D866FB" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Lachnaceae" genus="L." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="L. novoguineensis subsp. var. var. yunnanicum" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="variety" species="novoguineensis" subSpecies="var." variety="yunnanicum">L. novoguineensis var. yunnanicum</taxonomicName>
(TNS-F-16442, 16642) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="70E93E3353A5D156E200DBCAEBDC088A" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. ML best-scored phylogenetic tree based on the concatenated dataset of ITS, LSU, mtSSU, and RPB 2 constructed using RAxML-NG. MLBP / MPBP / BPP are represented on branches in this order. In MLBP / MPBP &lt;50 % or BPP &lt;0.95, a hyphen appears. No evaluation values are shown on branches when MLBP and MPBP &lt;50 % and BPP &lt;0.95. The branch of a clade TNS-F- 17245 + 17249 to its most recent common ancestor is only one-third of the intended length due to space limitation." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.87.73082.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/643408" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">1</figureCitation>
) and occurs in the same habitats (that is, bamboo sheaths) but has shorter asci and ascospores. The ascal bases of the two species are very characteristic, in that they have croziers with perforations (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="C4C9109B6440622DAB5FB0CE4F677585" captionStart="Figure 15" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figure 15. Erioscyphella sasibrevispora TNS-F- 81401 (Holotype, A-F, H-J). Lachnum novoguineense var. yunnanicum TNS-F- 16442 (G) A dried apothecia B a pure culture on PDA (NBRC 114475) C ectal excipular cells D ascus E an ascal pore MLZ (+) F ascal base with a perforated crozier G ascal base with a perforated crozier H septated paraphyses I ascospores J vertical section through the apothecium. Mounted in CB / LA (D, F-J), MLZ (E). Scale bars: 1 mm (A); 10 µm (C-J)." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.87.73082.figure15" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/643422" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">15G</figureCitation>
and Fig. 
<figureCitation id="CAD7ACE40635678B40EAB265F6E47414" captionStart="Figure 16" captionStartId="F16" captionText="Figure 16. Erioscyphella sasibrevispora TNS-F- 81401 (Holotype A-D, F, G). Lachnum novoguineense var. yunnanicum TNS-F- 16642 (E) A apothecium B vertical section of an apothecium C ascospores D asci (with basal structures sometimes with perforation) E ascal base arising from a crozier with perforation F paraphyses G ectal excipular cells H hairs." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.87.73082.figure16" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/643423" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">16E</figureCitation>
). In 
<taxonomicName id="2D94E96CF028B5991938DE57EBF5AD6B" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Lachnaceae" genus="L." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="family">Lachnaceae</taxonomicName>
, this type of crozier has only been reported in 
<taxonomicName id="E4D2DDBA8A8C6A27035824D37A811191" authorityName="P.A.Karsten" authorityYear="1884" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Hyaloscyphaceae" genus="Lachnellula" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lachnellula" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="F21999A9250B783252F882BE4A3B0721" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Lachnellula</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="6EA7A7368B529772BAF4AFEB140C1C22" author="Baral, HO" journalOrPublisher="Beitraege zur Kenntnis der Pilze Mitteleuropas" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="143 - 156" refId="B3" refString="Baral, HO, 1984. Taxonomische und oekologische Studien ueber die Koniferen bewohnenden europaeischen Arten der Gattung Lachnellula Karsten. Beitraege zur Kenntnis der Pilze Mitteleuropas 1: 143 - 156" title="Taxonomische und oekologische Studien ueber die Koniferen bewohnenden europaeischen Arten der Gattung Lachnellula Karsten." volume="1" year="1984">Baral 1984</bibRefCitation>
). Additionally, both species exceptionally lack any hair materials in 
<taxonomicName id="0B8F75D426F880A55879586A057CE502" authorityName="Kirschstein" authorityYear="1938" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Lachnaceae" genus="Erioscyphella" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Erioscyphella" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="C0251CCAEC667DA197CC5F7A1F5E0DE8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Erioscyphella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
