<paragraph id="741D70B1956F7ADA776AEBBEF0EA5265" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
The tropical species 
<taxonomicName id="C71B92689D8846B6E5CC790BAA1F2FF2" genus="E." lsidName="E. bambusina" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="bambusina">
<emphasis id="E888219137F2FABCE948C89C2017A97E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">E. bambusina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="B03DC4AD2BA360D0213CFEF7E7E2E4E7" class="Ascomycetes" family="Discomycetes" genus="Lachnum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lachnum albidum subsp. var. var. americanum" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="variety" species="albidum" subSpecies="var." variety="americanum">Lachnum albidum var. americanum</taxonomicName>
(Dennis) W.Y. Zhuang also occur on bamboo sheaths. However, compared with the present fungus, the former has smaller ascospores and filiform paraphyses (
<bibRefCitation id="45E3EDD73AD64F8882C5A2046CEE3360" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114399" author="Dennis, RWG" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="289 - 348" refId="B15" refString="Dennis, RWG, 1954. Some inoperculate discomycetes of tropical America. Kew Bulletin 9 (2): 289 - 348, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4114399" title="Some inoperculate discomycetes of tropical America." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114399" volume="9" year="1954">Dennis 1954</bibRefCitation>
), and the latter has extremely large asci and ascospores (
<bibRefCitation id="EC706A178AA747CC86A37A23029BBBCA" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114758" author="Dennis, RWG" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="418 - 458" refId="B16" refString="Dennis, RWG, 1960. Fungi venezuelani: III. Kew Bulletin 14 (3): 418 - 458, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4114758" title="Fungi venezuelani: III." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4114758" volume="14" year="1960">Dennis 1960</bibRefCitation>
). In cool-temperate to subarctic zones, 
<taxonomicName id="BCA11FDD0306113592E37E3C7AA17A1E" class="Leotiomycetes" family="Lachnaceae" genus="L." kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="L. asiaticum" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="asiaticum">
<emphasis id="D8165DAC4A40E4809585CBF8FCC0426C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">L. asiaticum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="2A15AA7C8A3A1F951622EE2486EF903D" class="Ascomycetes" family="Discomycetes" genus="Lachnum" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Lachnum sasae" order="Helotiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="sasae">
<emphasis id="5C2013627082F3FEA816233D941A5EC3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Lachnum sasae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Raitv. occur on bamboo sheaths (
<bibRefCitation id="3C1227230F515B031884B7CB3A89E38F" author="Otani, Y" journalOrPublisher="Transactions of the Mycological Society of Japan" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="33 - 42" refId="B55" refString="Otani, Y, 1967. Notes on some cup fungi of the Hyaloscyphaceae collected in Hokkaido, Japan. Transactions of the Mycological Society of Japan 8: 33 - 42" title="Notes on some cup fungi of the Hyaloscyphaceae collected in Hokkaido, Japan." volume="8" year="1967">Otani 1967</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="B52A76C6EEE72C41A71FC2162A89FCBF" author="Raitviir, A" journalOrPublisher="Novosti Sistematiki Nizshikh Rastenii" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" pagination="157 - 162" refId="B59" refString="Raitviir, A, 1985. Species Hyaloscyphacearum in Sasa spp. inventae. Novosti Sistematiki Nizshikh Rastenii 22: 157 - 162" title="Species Hyaloscyphacearum in Sasa spp. inventae." volume="22" year="1985">Raitviir 1985</bibRefCitation>
), but their ascospores are much shorter than those of the present fungus.
</paragraph>
